Note:
Scala Translation Round-Trip Probe

End-to-end proof that the Scala translation pipeline is REAL, not a skeleton:

    Scala source
      -> scala_lexer    (tokenizer)
      -> scala_parser   (recursive-descent AST: package, imports, object,
                         case class, trait + class, generic def with bounds,
                         match w/ patterns + guard, for-comprehension w/ yield,
                         lambda, string interpolation)
      -> scala_semantic (scope/name analysis; validation only)
      -> scala_to_hir   (lower to the producer's HIRNode tree IR)
      -> hir_to_scala   (emit HIR back to valid Scala text)
      -> re-lex / re-parse / re-to_hir of the emitted text
      -> structural HIR equality on the key constructs

The Scala HIR node model is scala_to_hir.runa's typed HIRNode record shared by
scala_to_hir (producer) and hir_to_scala (consumer): each node is a struct with
node_type at offset 8, the textual value at offset 16, and a children List at
offset 24. This probe reads HIR fields through exactly that contract.

It lowers the source to HIR1, asserts HIR1 is a module whose tree contains the
named declarations (object "Geometry", case class "Circle", trait "Shape",
class "Square", def "area", def "classify"), emits HIR1 back to Scala text,
re-runs the whole pipeline on the emitted text to HIR2, and asserts HIR2 is
STRUCTURALLY EQUAL to HIR1 on those same key constructs.

Exit code: number of failed assertions (0 == all passed). No exit_with_code.
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/scala/scala_to_hir.runa" as ScalaFrontend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/scala/hir_to_scala.runa" as ScalaBackend
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as TestUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: HIRNode decoders - node_type@8, value@16, children@24, matching
Note: scala_to_hir.runa's HIRNode record (node_id@0, node_type@8, value@16,
Note: children@24, attributes@32, type_info@40, source_location@48).
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
The node_type tag lives at offset 8 (node_id occupies offset 0). Centralising the
read documents the contract this probe shares with both producer and consumer.
@End Reasoning
Process called "hir_kind" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 8
End Process

@Reasoning:
The textual payload (name / literal / identifier) is the String handle at offset
16.
@End Reasoning
Process called "hir_value" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 16
End Process

@Reasoning:
The children List handle is at offset 24; the same List the producer populated
via add_hir_child, so List.length / List.get iterate it directly.
@End Reasoning
Process called "hir_children" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 24
End Process

@Reasoning:
The child count is the length of the children list, or 0 when the node has no
children handle.
@End Reasoning
Process called "hir_child_count" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc hir_children with node
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc list_length from List with children
End Process

@Reasoning:
Positional child access over the children list.
@End Reasoning
Process called "hir_child" takes node as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc hir_children with node
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc list_get from List with children, index
End Process

@Reasoning:
Recursively searches the whole HIR tree for the first node whose value string
equals the requested name. Robust locator for a named declaration regardless of
the depth (module -> package -> class/trait body) at which it sits.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_named_any" takes parent as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    If parent is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pv be proc hir_value with parent
    If pv is not equal to 0:
        Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with pv, name
        If matches is equal to 1:
            Return parent
        End If
    End If
    Let count be proc hir_child_count with parent
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let child be proc hir_child with parent, i
        Let found be proc find_named_any with child, name
        If found is not equal to 0:
            Return found
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Two HIR nodes are structurally equal on a construct when both carry the same
node_type tag - a whitespace-insensitive fidelity check that survives the
emitter's re-indentation.
@End Reasoning
Process called "same_kind" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ka be proc hir_kind with a
    Let kb be proc hir_kind with b
    If ka is equal to kb:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Probe entry point
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be proc create_test_results from TestUtils
    proc begin_suite from TestUtils with results, "Scala translation round-trip"

    Note:
    Representative program exercising the constructs the task requires: a package,
    imports (wildcard + selector), an object, a case class, a trait and a class
    extending it, a generic def with an upper bound, a match with patterns and a
    guard, a for-comprehension with yield, a lambda, and string interpolation.
    :End Note
    Let source be "package geometry\nimport scala.collection.mutable._\nimport scala.math.{Pi, sqrt}\nobject Geometry {\nval origin = 0\n}\ncase class Circle(radius: Double)\ntrait Shape {\ndef area: Double\n}\nclass Square(side: Double) extends Shape {\ndef area: Double = side * side\n}\ndef classify[T <: Shape](s: T): String = s match {\ncase c if c.area > 10.0 => \"big\"\ncase _ => \"small\"\n}\ndef pairs = for (x <- List(1, 2, 3)) yield x * 2\nval f = (x: Int) => x + 1\nval label = s\"area\"\n"

    Note: --- Stage 0-2: source -> HIR1 (parse, validate, lower) ---
    Let hir1 be proc scala_to_hir_from_source from ScalaFrontend with source
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "frontend produced HIR module", hir1

    Note: HIR root has declarations.
    Let root_kids be proc hir_child_count with hir1
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "module has declarations", root_kids, 0

    Note: --- key named constructs present in HIR1 ---
    Let obj_node be proc find_named_any with hir1, "Geometry"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "object 'Geometry' lowered", obj_node

    Let circle_node be proc find_named_any with hir1, "Circle"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "case class 'Circle' lowered", circle_node

    Let shape_node be proc find_named_any with hir1, "Shape"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "trait 'Shape' lowered", shape_node

    Let square_node be proc find_named_any with hir1, "Square"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "class 'Square' lowered", square_node

    Let classify_node be proc find_named_any with hir1, "classify"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "def 'classify' lowered", classify_node

    Let area_node be proc find_named_any with hir1, "area"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "def 'area' lowered", area_node

    Note: --- Stage 3: HIR1 -> Scala text ---
    Let emitted be proc hir_to_scala from ScalaBackend with hir1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "backend produced Scala text", emitted
    Let emitted_len be proc string_length from StringCore with emitted
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "emitted Scala is non-empty", emitted_len, 0

    Note: --- Stage 4: re-run the pipeline on the emitted text -> HIR2 ---
    Let hir2 be proc scala_to_hir_from_source from ScalaFrontend with emitted
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "re-parse of emitted Scala produced HIR", hir2
    Let root2_kids be proc hir_child_count with hir2
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "round-trip module has declarations", root2_kids, 0

    Note: --- Stage 5: structural equality on the key constructs ---
    Let obj2 be proc find_named_any with hir2, "Geometry"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves object 'Geometry'", obj2
    Let obj_same be proc same_kind with obj_node, obj2
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves 'Geometry' node kind", obj_same, 1

    Let circle2 be proc find_named_any with hir2, "Circle"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves case class 'Circle'", circle2
    Let circle_same be proc same_kind with circle_node, circle2
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves 'Circle' node kind", circle_same, 1

    Let shape2 be proc find_named_any with hir2, "Shape"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves trait 'Shape'", shape2

    Let square2 be proc find_named_any with hir2, "Square"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves class 'Square'", square2

    Let classify2 be proc find_named_any with hir2, "classify"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves def 'classify'", classify2

    proc print_summary from TestUtils with results
    Let failed be proc get_failed from TestUtils with results
    proc destroy_test_results from TestUtils with results

    Return failed
End Process
